## Part 7: Color Tokens (Tailwind)

```typescript
// BRAND KIT — Laguna Beach Palette (March 2026)
colors: {
  brand: {
    'pacific-dusk': '#1B3A5C',     // Primary text, headings
    'deep-water': '#0F2237',       // Dark backgrounds, hero sections
    'victoria-cove': '#2E8B8B',    // Links, focus states, clarity
    'thousand-steps': '#C4963C',   // Prestige accent (sparingly)
    'sunset-cliff': '#E8834A',     // Primary CTA color
    'sandstone': '#F5F0E5',        // Warm surface, section backgrounds
    'morning-light': '#FAF8F4',    // Default background
    'salt-air': '#FFFFFF',         // White
    'tide-pool': '#3A8B6E',        // Success, positive states
    'sage-hill': '#7A8B6E',        // Secondary green
    'driftwood': '#B8A88A',        // Neutral accent
  },
  // Legacy compatibility (maps to Brand Kit)
  lbta: {
    orange: '#E8834A',      // Sunset Cliff
    red: '#F04E23',         // Legacy — avoid in new code
    beige: '#F5F0E5',       // Sandstone
    black: '#0A0A0A',       // Rich black
    white: '#FFFFFF',
    cream: '#FAF8F4',       // Morning Light
    charcoal: '#1B3A5C',    // Pacific Dusk
  }
}
```

**Color Usage Rules:**
- Never use more than 3 colors in a single section
- **Buttons**: Black/white for primary CTAs; Sunset Cliff (#E8834A) for hover/accent only
- **Links/Focus**: Victoria Cove (#2E8B8B)
- **Backgrounds**: Morning Light (#FAF8F4) default, Sandstone (#F5F0E5) warm sections, Deep Water (#0F2237) dark sections, Deep Card (#0A1628) for elevated dark cards on light pages
- **Text**: Pacific Dusk (#1B3A5C) for headings/body, use opacity variants for secondary text
- Prefer `brand-*` classes for new code; `lbta-*` for backwards compat only
- **Brand Guide**: Visual and section accents follow the LBTA Brand Guide — horizon gradient (`--horizon`), `.section-quote` for pull quotes, and HorizonDivider or `.section-horizon` under key section headings.

**Hex literals — single source of truth (locked v1.1, 2026-05-05):**
- All brand hex values live in `tokens/lbta-web-tokens.json`. Tailwind classes, CSS vars, and TS constants are all generated from it.
- **Never hardcode `'#XXXXXX'`** in `app/` or `components/`. CI fails in strict mode.
- For TS logic (computed accent colors, charts, canvas): `import { BRAND } from '@/lib/brand-tokens'` and use `BRAND.victoriaCove`, `BRAND.deepWater`, etc.
- For inline styles or CSS-in-JS: prefer `var(--brand-…)` over `BRAND.…`.
- For arbitrary Tailwind values: forbidden — `bg-[#0a1628]` ❌ → `bg-brand-deep-card` ✅.
- Visual proof of system: `/brand` route (internal, noindex). See `docs/brand-token-system.md`.

**Email templates (`assets/emails/**/*.html`) — separate ruleset (locked v1.2, 2026-05-11):**
- Tracked email templates are scanned by the same `tokens:check` script in both `--all` and edited-files mode.
- **Forbidden hex** (consolidated to a brand token): currently `#d5d1ca` → `lbta-stone (#E8E4DF)`. Adding more to `emailForbiddenHexes` in `scripts/check-brand-usage.ts` strict-blocks new violations. **WARN → ERROR in strict.**
- **CAN-SPAM postal address**: customer-facing templates (containing "Laguna Beach") MUST contain `1098 Balboa`. **ERROR (legal compliance, §316.5).** AC placeholder stub `lbta-spring-2026.html` is exempt.
- Generic body grays (`#333`, `#666`, `#999`, `#667788`) are explicitly **allowed** in `lib/email.ts` per the BRAND COLOR POLICY comment header (visual hierarchy + email-design convention). See `docs/brand-token-system.md` Guardrails → Email templates.

**Two namespaces by design — `brand.*` and `lbta.*`:**
- **`brand-*`** = 12 brand identity colors (the Pacific palette + `brand-deep-card`). Use for everything brand-related.
- **`lbta-*`** = 4 system utility colors only:
  - `lbta-slate` (#6B6B6B) — neutral secondary text
  - `lbta-stone` (#E8E4DF) — neutral border / disabled / divider
  - `lbta-red` (#F04E23) — **error/alert only**, never marketing
  - `lbta-black` (#0A0A0A) — true black for premium CTAs
- **Any other `lbta-*` name is deprecated** (lbta-cream, lbta-charcoal, lbta-orange, lbta-beige, lbta-sand, lbta-bone, lbta-burnt, lbta-coral, lbta-coral-dark, lbta-primary, lbta-secondary). The checker fails strict mode if any appear in new code. Migrate per `docs/brand-token-system.md` mapping table.

**Hand-rolled eyebrow patterns (now strict-mode enforced):**
- Use `text-eyebrow` (0.7rem, 0.18em tracking) or `text-eyebrow-sm` (0.65rem, 0.12em tracking). **Never** hand-roll `text-[10-12px] uppercase tracking-[N]` — CI will fail.
- The only allowed exception: responsive size jumps in hero contexts, e.g. `text-[11px] md:text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em]`. The checker explicitly excludes these. There are 7 documented instances site-wide.
- All other historical hand-rolled eyebrows were migrated in v1.3 (commit ddd76e6 → bd702bf → e7fa23d → next). 230 instances cleaned in one pass.

